           Here it is i have a goranga spiked club in my primary hand but in my off hand i can have either a fighting baton or cane of the tranguil(sp) both have the same ratio should i go with cot over the baton because of higher damage/ delay or do both hand swing independantly of each other? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uazathool.showPublicProfile?language=EN>azathool</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 950<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/30/02 12:37:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11657.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.azathool.com/IMAGES/moving-aza.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: off hand question</span><hr size=1> Both swing independantly, and there is no &quot;damage&quot; bonus for off hand weapons.<br>
<br>
So a 10/20 does the same damage as a 14/28 offhand.<br>
<br>
Therefore, you want the best <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> ratio</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> in off hand.<br>
<br>
ie, a 18/25 is better than a 12/20 in off hand (not taking into account procs and stats/ac etc).<br>
